From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 14:55:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] backends/native/drm-lease: complete bookkeeping when kernel
 has already auto-revoked the lease

When a DRM lease holder closes its lease fd (e.g. SteamVR's vrcompositor
exits or crashes), the kernel auto-revokes the lease. The next time
mutter's meta_drm_lease_revoke() runs against that MetaDrmLease, the
DRM_IOCTL_MODE_REVOKE_LEASE ioctl returns -ENOENT because the kernel
has no record of the lease anymore.

The current code logs a warning and returns early without calling
mark_revoked(). That early return is wrong: it leaves the lease's
LeasingKmsAssignment list in place, each of which holds a CRTC with
meta_kms_crtc_set_is_leased (crtc, TRUE). Mutter's atomic commit code
still believes those CRTCs are leased to someone else and emits the
CRTC into the atomic state in a configuration the kernel rejects with
EINVAL. The visible symptom is

    Direct scanout page flip failed: drmModeAtomicCommit: Invalid argument
    Page flip failed: drmModeAtomicCommit: Invalid argument
    Failed to post KMS update: drmModeAtomicCommit: Invalid argument

followed by no further frames reaching the desktop monitors (input still
flows, mutter's main loop is alive, but scanout is wedged). The user
sees this as "windows go weird, can't click, frozen-but-not-quite";
switching to a VT and back forces a DRM reset and recovers.

ENOENT from drmModeRevokeLease() is not a failure -- it is the normal
result of "the kernel beat us to it." Treat it as success and proceed
with mark_revoked(), which calls meta_drm_lease_unassign() (clears
is_leased on each CRTC) and emits the LEASE_REVOKED signal so the lease
manager can finalize its state.

For any other errno (real failure), keep the current behaviour: log,
do not clean up bookkeeping (because the lease really is still active
in the kernel).

Forwarded: no
Last-Update: 2026-05-20
Index: mutter-50.1/src/backends/native/meta-drm-lease.c
===================================================================
--- mutter-50.1.orig/src/backends/native/meta-drm-lease.c
+++ mutter-50.1/src/backends/native/meta-drm-lease.c
@@ -411,6 +411,20 @@ meta_drm_lease_revoke (MetaDrmLease *lea
 
   if (!meta_kms_device_revoke_lease (lease->kms_device, lease->lessee_id, &error))
     {
+      /* If the kernel has already auto-revoked the lease (because the
+       * lease holder closed its fd, e.g. vrcompositor crashed or exited),
+       * the ioctl returns ENOENT. That is not a failure on our part --
+       * the lease really is gone -- and we still need to complete the
+       * bookkeeping (clear is_leased on the CRTCs, emit LEASE_REVOKED,
+       * zero the lessee_id) so subsequent atomic commits do not include
+       * those CRTCs in a kernel-incompatible state.
+       */
+      if (g_error_matches (error, G_IO_ERROR, G_IO_ERROR_NOT_FOUND))
+        {
+          mark_revoked (lease);
+          return;
+        }
+
       g_warning ("Failed to revoke DRM lease on %s: %s",
                  meta_kms_device_get_path (lease->kms_device),
                  error->message);
